        <mxCell id="ObN9QLPdV3uD9SNAZ5Un-28" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=0;orthogonalLoop=1;jettySize=auto;html=1;" parent="1" source="ObN9QLPdV3uD9SNAZ5Un-23" target="ObN9QLPdV3uD9SNAZ5Un-26" edge="1" visible="0">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="ObN9QLPdV3uD9SNAZ5Un-23" value="&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;Features&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span&gt;The functional design is also known as the U-form organisation. U stands for&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;Unity. It is characterized by simultaneous combination of similar activities into&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;department according to their main functional areas.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div&gt; A functional structure groups the tasks and activities by business functions such&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;as marketing, Finance, HR, Production, R&amp;amp;D etc., Each major function is divided&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;into major function here.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; It consists of Corporate Level (CEO or MD) and Functional Level (Managers of&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;each function)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; Functional heads are not responsible for overall results of the organization.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Companies following a single business strategy and offer a line of products in a&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;single market may require simple structures. Such structures are recommended&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;for cost leadership and focused differentiation.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" parent="1" vertex="1" visible="0">
          <mxGeometry x="-152.5" y="1120" width="450" height="250" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="ObN9QLPdV3uD9SNAZ5Un-25" value="&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;Advantages of Functional Structure&amp;nbsp;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- Simple structure&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- Least expensive&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- Provides specialization in&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span&gt;functions&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- Most suitable for small firms&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- Improves operational efficiencies&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- Enables quick in decision making&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- Minimises duplication of tasks&amp;nbsp;&lt;span&gt;and functions.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- Promotes common values and&amp;nbsp;&lt;span&gt;goals&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- among employees&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- If Better co-ordination among&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;departments exist, it leads to&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;competitive advantage.&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" parent="1" vertex="1" visible="0">
          <mxGeometry x="-227.5" y="1410" width="280" height="350" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="ObN9QLPdV3uD9SNAZ5Un-26" value="&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;Disadvantages of Functional Structure&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- No Accountability. Only top level is&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;accountable for organizational&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span&gt;goals&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- Minimises career development&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;opportunities&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- Low employee morale&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- Creates conflicts among&amp;nbsp;&lt;span&gt;departments&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- Specialisation may kill overall&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;innovation&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- Communication gaps among various&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;departments&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- Not suitable for multi business and&amp;nbsp;&lt;span&gt;multi&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- product firms usually&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" parent="1" vertex="1" visible="0">
          <mxGeometry x="92.5" y="1410" width="280" height="350" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
