        <mxCell id="ObN9QLPdV3uD9SNAZ5Un-67" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=0;orthogonalLoop=1;jettySize=auto;html=1;" parent="1" source="ObN9QLPdV3uD9SNAZ5Un-62" target="ObN9QLPdV3uD9SNAZ5Un-65" edge="1" visible="0">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="ObN9QLPdV3uD9SNAZ5Un-62" value="&lt;div&gt;This type of the structure is created by deputing functional specialist to work on specific&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;project / products. These specialist from different functional areas form a group or team&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;and report to the team leader (project manager).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Once the project is completed, they, go back to the representative respective&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;department. Each employee will be assigned to one Functional manager and further to&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Project manager too. Thus, employees have 2 superiors.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;This structure is found to be suitable for large &amp;amp; complex organizations which&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;require more flexibility. Employees will have two superiors, a product / project&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;manager and a functional manager.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" parent="1" vertex="1" visible="0">
          <mxGeometry x="387.5" y="1290" width="480" height="160" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="ObN9QLPdV3uD9SNAZ5Un-64" value="&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;Advantages of Matrix Structure&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- Most suitable for construction&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;firms, R&amp;amp;D, labs, Health care.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- Clarity in project objectives&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- Employees can see the visible&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;results of their work through&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;many channels of&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;communication.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- Project shut down is accomplished&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;easily.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- Encouraging generation of&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;new ideas because of pooling of&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;diverse elements&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" parent="1" vertex="1" visible="0">
          <mxGeometry x="327.5" y="1490" width="280" height="350" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="ObN9QLPdV3uD9SNAZ5Un-65" value="&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;Disadvantages&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- Very expensive, due to more&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;management positions.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- More complex, due to&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;horizontal and vertical flow of&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;authority and communication&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- Dual authority and reporting&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;leading to confusion.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- Sharing of authority between project&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;managers and functional managers&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;results in confrontation / conflicts.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" parent="1" vertex="1" visible="0">
