        <mxCell id="ObN9QLPdV3uD9SNAZ5Un-72" value="&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;Disadvantages of Network Structure:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;• Lack of coordination and control due to numerous partners.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;• Several functions are contracted to separate suppliers or distributors. It may be&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;difficult to discover synergy benefits by combining different activities.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;• If a particular firm overspecializes in only few functions, it may choose wrong&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;function and thus become non - competitive.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;• New structures may create stress for many employees.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;• New structures often demand new skills, many workers may not adopt to it and&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;may not perform well&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;• Employees may lack confidence to participate organization sponsored learning&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;programs.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" parent="1" vertex="1" visible="0">
